Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.07,0:01:34.82,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:93072,94824}Hot! Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:46.66,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:103916,106669}John? I'm leaving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:01.68,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:119682,121684}Jules Verne, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.35,0:02:04.85,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:123353,124854}I read his works, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:08.65,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:127815,128650}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:13.69,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:132028,133696}Good morning, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:18.57,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:135073,138576}Oh, right!\NI'm going to be late for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.57,0:02:21.87,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:138576,141871}I'm going out now,\Nbut I made you breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:23.08,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:141871,143081}Where's Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.08,0:02:25.58,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:143081,145583}She's been at\NHamilton's since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:27.54,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:145583,147543}A difficult delivery, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:28.79,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:147543,148795}I see…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.79,0:02:32.79,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:149796,152799}The baby's not born yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:34.30,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:153341,154300}See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.71,0:02:39.09,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:154717,159097}Oh, I might be late today,\Nso take care of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.09,0:02:41.39,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:159097,161391}Mom should be back by noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:43.30,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:161391,163309}Hey, is it a boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.06,0:02:45.81,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:164060,165812}Oh? What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.31,0:02:49.02,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:166312,169023}Mrs. Hamilton's baby, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:51.23,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:169023,171234}I sure hope it's a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:55.32,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:171234,175321}If it is, I'll take him\Nto the hill of the Rocky Heath.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:00.49,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:179075,180493}Have a nice day at work!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.49,0:03:01.36,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:180493,181369}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.09,0:03:17.21,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:196092,197218}All right, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.09,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:197218,198094}Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.31,0:03:30.10,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:209313,210106}Good morning, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:31.14,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:210106,211149}Good morning, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:33.15,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:211607,213151}Hey, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:34.52,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:213151,214527}Good morning, Kevin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:35.52,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:214527,215528}Good morning, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:37.15,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:215528,217155}Good morning.\NWe rely on you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:38.48,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:217613,218489}Good morning, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:39.49,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:218489,219490}Yeah, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.49,0:03:40.03,lassie default,Worker,0,0,0,,{TIME:219490,220032}Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:41.65,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:220032,221659}How are things today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:54.29,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:232128,234297}This is the tastiest way to eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.26,0:04:04.26,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:242263,244265}Thanks for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:11.31,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:248269,251314}I'm leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.24,0:04:26.12,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:263242,266120}Well, it's not like anybody's gonna answer.\NI'm all alone today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:28.87,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:266120,268873}Be careful, John!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:31.37,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:269290,271375}I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:39.09,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:276672,279091}Right. Before I go to school…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:46.68,lassie default,Grandma Forrester,0,0,0,,{TIME:284388,286682}John Carraclough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:51.18,lassie default,Grandma Forrester,0,0,0,,{TIME:287642,291187}Where are you going?\NThis is not the way to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:55.35,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:291854,295358}I haven't said "good morning"\Nto my mother yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:56.94,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:295358,296943}So I'm going to\NMrs. Hamilton's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:04:58.61,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:296943,298611}Have a nice day, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.45,0:05:14.50,lassie default,Housewife,0,0,0,,{TIME:311457,314502}Melissa, your son's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.33,0:05:19.50,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:316337,319507}Just a minute.\NI can't exactly talk to him right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.96,0:05:22.71,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:319966,322718}What are you talking about,\NMrs. Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:25.09,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:322718,325096}At least say\N"good morning" to your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.09,0:05:26.59,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:325096,326597}Oh, Doctor…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:34.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:332770,334063}Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.64,0:05:37.40,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:334647,337400}Good morning, John.\NDid you eat your breakfast today?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.40,0:05:39.77,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:337400,339777}Yes. Dad made it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:42.98,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:340528,342989}It must be tough for you,\Nstaying up all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:45.49,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:343906,345491}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:48.20,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:345491,348202}The lady who gives birth to the baby\Nalways has it the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:50.78,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:348202,350788}The entire night passed\Nand the baby still didn't come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.33,0:05:56.46,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:353332,356460}Oh, good, good.\NYou're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:58.17,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:356460,358170}Mrs. Carraclough!\NI need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:01.29,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:359422,361299}If all goes smooth,\NI'll be back before lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:02.88,lassie default,Melissa Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:362049,362884}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:04.30,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:363467,364302}Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.15,0:06:24.32,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:383154,384322}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:25.65,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:384322,385656}Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.61,0:06:27.86,lassie default,Sam Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:386616,387867}I see.
